## Task: Create status page routes in App Router

### Problem
Status page components exist in `src/widgets/status/` but have no App Router pages. Features already route to these paths (e.g. `router.push(getRouteSuccess())` which will resolve to `/cards/success`).

### Existing exports in `src/widgets/status/index.ts`
```ts
export { HelloPage, ErrorPage, SuccessPage, DeclinePage } from './ui';
```

All status components are `'use client'` components.

### Create 4 new files

**1. `/Users/zeizel/projects/mlm/app/cards/success/page.tsx`**
```tsx
import { SuccessPage } from '@/widgets/status';

export default function Success() {
	return <SuccessPage />;
}
```

**2. `/Users/zeizel/projects/mlm/app/cards/error/page.tsx`**
```tsx
import { ErrorPage } from '@/widgets/status';

export default function Error() {
	return <ErrorPage />;
}
```

**3. `/Users/zeizel/projects/mlm/app/cards/decline/page.tsx`**
```tsx
import { DeclinePage } from '@/widgets/status';

export default function Decline() {
	return <DeclinePage />;
}
```

**4. `/Users/zeizel/projects/mlm/app/cards/hello/page.tsx`**
```tsx
import { HelloPage } from '@/widgets/status';

export default function Hello() {
	return <HelloPage />;
}
```

### IMPORTANT
- These are server component wrappers that render client widgets
- Do NOT modify any existing files
- Only CREATE the 4 new page files
- Use tabs for indentation (project convention)

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] 4 new page files created under app/cards/
- [ ] Each imports from @/widgets/status
- [ ] Each is a default export server component
